Course Overview

This is the One-Stop Test Series to get recruited in one of the worldâ€™s best tech companies i.e. Amazon. This test series covers all possible questions that Amazon can ask in coding interview rounds.

The test series is designed keeping under consideration all important topics of Data Structures and Algorithms that Amazon can exclusively put forward for hiring. It has few dedicated test sections that drive the test-takers through all the realms of Amazon test experience and contests.

FAQs

  1. How much does the subscription to the test series cost?
    The fee for this test series is Rs 499.
     
  2. How can I register for this test series?
    Click on the Signup for free button. Pay fees online.
     
  3. What are the available payment methods?
    The payment of the test series subscription can be done via online banking, credit/debit cards, UPI(Google pay, Paytm, Phone pay, etc). 
     
  4. What is the duration of each test?  
    The duration of each test is 60 mins.
     
  5. I have purchased DSA courses from GeeksforGeeks. Is Amazon Test Series still beneficial for me?
    Amazon Test Series may contain some repeated problems from DSA courses. However, you will still get some additional problems to solve specifically asked in Amazon Interviews, also we will keep on adding new practice problems to tracks. Moreover, we have 10 practice contests that are completely unique and designed specifically based on Amazon coding interview rounds which are not available in any of the DSA courses.
     
  6. Does the test expire if I do not take it on time?
    No, the test doesnÊ¼t expire. You can take the test anytime after its start date as per your convenience.
     
  7. What are the programming languages supported in the contests?
    The participants can submit their codes in C++ or Java or Python.
     
  8. Do We Get any Placement Assistance?
    Opportunities from the different companies can be viewed on the hiring platform where you can see their current opening & once you have enrolled for this course you can apply for any of the opening(s).
